Ker(T_A)
         \begin{pmatrix}         1 & 2\\         0 & 3 \\         \end{pmatrix}X-X    \begin{pmatrix}         1 & 2\\         0 & 3 \\         \end{pmatrix}=\begin{pmatrix}         0 & 0\\         0 & 0 \\         \end{pmatrix} 
\begin{cases} a_1+2a_3-a_1=0\\ a_2+2a_4-2a_1-3a_2=0\\ 3a_3-a_3=0\\ 3a_4-2a_3+3a_4=0 \end{cases} 
X=\begin{pmatrix}         a & b\\         c & d \\         \end{pmatrix}
AX-XA=\begin{pmatrix}         2c & (2d-2b-2a)\\         2c & -2c \\         \end{pmatrix}=\begin{pmatrix}         0 & 0\\         0 & 0 \\         \end{pmatrix}\iff (c=0)\land (d=b+a)
\operatorname{ker}(T_A)=\operatorname{span}\Bigg(I_2,\begin{pmatrix}         0 & 1\\         0 & 1 \\         \end{pmatrix}\Bigg)
\operatorname{Im}(T_A)=\operatorname{span}\Bigg(\begin{pmatrix}         1 & 0\\         1 & -1 \\         \end{pmatrix},\begin{pmatrix}         0 & 1\\         0 & 0 \\         \end{pmatrix}\Bigg)
